{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b8510622-2629-468f-8b5d-39194ea54db9","content":"In .NET 10 MAUI, the iOS-specific `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` was replaced with a **cross-platform** `Page.SafeAreaRegions` property. Replace:\n\n```xml\n<!-- .NET 9 (remove this) -->\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\nwith:\n\n```xml\n<!-- .NET 10 -->\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"All\">\n```\n\n`SafeAreaRegions` is a flags enum, so you can also be selective:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Only respect top and bottom safe areas -->\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"Top,Bottom\">\n```\n\nAvailable values: `None`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, `Right`, `All`.\n\nYou can also remove the `xmlns:ios` namespace declaration if it's no longer used elsewhere. No code-behind changes needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4b8de83e-f298-4cc2-8092-886ca1cd3fc8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI migration issue from .NET 9 to .NET 10 regarding safe area handling on iOS. This is a known breaking change in .NET 10 MAUI.\n\nIn .NET 10, the `UseSafeArea` attached property was removed/changed. The new approach uses padding-based safe area insets or the new `SafeAreaRegions` API.\n\nLet me recall what I know:\n\nIn .NET 10 (MAUI), the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` property was replaced. The new approach is to use `SafeAreaRegions` property which is available on `Page`. The property is cross-platform now, not iOS-specific.\n\n\nThe replacement is the `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page`, which accepts flag values like `None`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, `Right`, or `All` to control which safe area regions the page respects. So instead of the old iOS-specific `UseSafeArea` boolean, you now specify exactly which edges should account for safe area insets.","outputTokens":690,"requestId":"B7CD:28DDBA:18EA46:2097ED:69FFDAF6"},"id":"8b2